    "title": "Motion: いく and くる, with へ",
    "explanation": "いく means 'to go' (away from here) and くる means 'to come' (toward here). The particle へ (pronounced 'e') marks the direction of movement: 海へいく (go toward the sea). かえる (帰る) means 'to return/go home.' These verbs combine naturally with に (goal) and から (origin).",
